<h2>What makes greytHR the compliance pick</h2>

<ul>
  <li><strong>PF and ESI</strong>, Auto-calculation, ECR generation, monthly compliance, year-end reconciliation. The edge cases (LOP, joiner-exiter mid-month, transfer cases) are handled correctly.</li>
  <li><strong>Professional Tax by state</strong>, India has 19 different PT slabs across states. greytHR maintains them all.</li>
  <li><strong>TDS and Form 16</strong>, Section 192 TDS, Form 16 generation, IT proof submission workflow, advance tax estimation.</li>
  <li><strong>Statutory bonus and gratuity</strong>, Calculation under Payment of Bonus Act and Payment of Gratuity Act.</li>
  <li><strong>LWF, IT proofs, attendance-linked deductions</strong>, The Indian payroll edge cases that catch younger HRMS products.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Where the AI helps</h2>

<h3>HR chatbot</h3>
<p>Routine employee questions (leave balance, payslip query, policy clarification) handled without HR intervention.</p>

<h3>Anomaly flagging</h3>
<p>Payroll run flags unusual amounts (mid-month resignations, missing attendance, sudden salary jumps) for review before disbursement.</p>

<h3>Compliance assistant</h3>
<p>"What is the latest PF wage ceiling?" "When is the next quarterly TDS return due?" Surfaces current Indian compliance requirements.</p>

<h2>Best Indian use cases</h2>

<h3>Indian SMEs (25-200 employees)</h3>
<p>The sweet spot. Payroll done right, statutory compliance handled, leave and attendance covered. Modern enough; trustworthy enough.</p>

<h3>Mid-market Indian companies (200-2,000 employees)</h3>
<p>Growth or Enterprise tier with custom workflows and SSO. Strong choice for compliance-conservative companies (manufacturing, traditional services).</p>

<h3>Companies with auditor-driven preferences</h3>
<p>If your auditor or CFO has used greytHR for past clients, the data structure and report formats are exactly what they expect.</p>

